commit_message: Commented out debugging print statements.
Added the Chlamy protein fasta database we used, along with the 3 files that comprise the Blast protein data base (the Chlre4_best_proteins.fasta.phr, .pin, and .psq files)
Fixed a gene coordinate bugwhen concatenating final Augustus output
Edits to the English in README.txt
Made the Augustus cfg file an optional argument.  Replace Exonerate 'splice3' and 'splice5' tags with their Augustus equivalents
Updated the input/output description in the README
Added a how-to run our python program annotate.py, and a brief description of the internals
Removed testing behavior that restricted analysis to only Contig412
Deleted the Contig file from the repository

Added functionality to parse and concatenate Augustus gff files, including one that generates a multi-fasta protein sequence files based on the protein sequences embedded in the Augustus gff files.  Also, added genome partitioning functionality--after blastx is run, the inputted DNA sequence is partitioned based on the Blastx hit
Finished rough draft implementation of our pipeline...added gff modifying functions to make Exonerate output compatible with Augustus, Augustus command line calls, and adjusted command line arguments

Added code to make individual fasta files all proteins in multi-fasta protein file.  Added exonerate section of the code--filter blastx output, and run exonerate on whole contigs + the proteins that matched the contig significatnly.  (A line in the blastx_fasta_files function restricts us to doing analysis on only contig 325 for simplicity right now)
Added annotate.py, our main driver
Deleted the chlamy protein sequence we aren't supposed to use.  Renamed main.py to annotate.py
Modified main.py so that it creates individual fasta files for each of the contigs, and runs blastx on each individual contig saving its output in its own xml file
Added main.py.  Our main driver for the project.
Added chlamy_rein.fasta which contains protein sequences for Chlamydomonas reinhardtii
Added a fasta file that contains only our selected contigs
Added a script that outputs a fasta file with only our contigs
Got rid of commented code in contig_explorer.py
Added a gitignore
Added a python script that explores the contigs in the scobliq.fasta database
Changed README to a .txt
Initial commit
